      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَمَّنِ اِشْتَرَى شَاةً وَ لَمْ يُعَرِّفْ بِهَا فَقَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ عَرَّفَ بِهَا، أَوْ لَمْ يُعَرِّفْ بِهَا »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3068 - Al-Bazanti narrated from Abdul Karim ibn Amr from Saeed ibn Yasar, who said: I asked Abu Abdullah (as) about someone who buys a sheep but does not announce it (as a sacrifice).\nImam (as) replied: \"There is no harm whether he announces it or does not announce it.\""
        ]
      }
